abstract: Prospect of Donald J Trump winning Republican presidential nomination has caused concern among Republicans in Congress, who worry he will not back party's conservative policy agenda; Trump stands in opposition to much of Republican orthodoxy, which House Speaker Paul D Ryan has spent much of last decade advancing.
lead_paragraph: As Mr. Trump inches closer to being the party’s presidential nominee, Republicans fear he won’t back the conservative agenda pushed by Mr. Ryan, the House speaker.

headline.main: Republican Race Puts Donald Trump and Paul Ryan on Collision Course
headline.print_headline: G.O.P. Fears What’s Next If Trump Can’t Be Stopped
